What the Game Looks Like:

This is a 2 player game similar to Candy Land.
There are 25 spaces on the board, with 4 special spaces.
Both players start on space 1.
The goal is to reach space 25.
Players take turns rolling a dice.

Board layout:

1 Start
10 Candy
15 Mud
20 Rainbow
22 Swamp
25 Finish

Rules:

Player1 goes first.
Each turn, the player rolls a 6 sided dice.
The player moves forward the number of spaces rolled.
If the player lands on a special space, an event happens-
Candy: move forward 2 spaces.
Mud: move backward 2 spaces.
Rainbow: move forward 3 spaces.
Swamp: move backward 4 spaces.
A player cannot go lower than space 1.
A player does not have to roll the exact number of spaces to land on space 25.
The first player to reach space 25 wins the game.

Functions Used:

loadGameData(filename)
Reads the game information from the text file
Stores each line into a list

displayGame(data)
Displays the current game state
Shows player positions and event spaces

movePlayer(data)
Finds whose turn it is
Rolls the dice
Moves the player
Checks for special event spaces
Updates player positions
Changes the turn to the next player

How Data Is Stored:

The game data is stored in a text file called events.txt.
This is the text it includes at the beginning of each game-
Turn: Player1
1: Player1
1: Player2
10: Candy
15: Mud
20: Rainbow
23: Swamp
Each line is stored in a list. The program reads the list and updates player positions during the game.
